00:01:03.620 --> 00:01:06.090
So at a fundamental
level, Project Tango

00:01:06.090 --> 00:01:10.800
stems from the observation
that today interactions

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:16.710
with our phones really ends at
the square box of the screen.

00:01:16.710 --> 00:01:19.620
And whether you're
at home browsing

00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:26.800
the internet for a new appliance
for your kitchen, or at work

00:01:26.800 --> 00:01:31.320
planning for a project
that you're going to build,

00:01:31.320 --> 00:01:37.860
or out at dinner socializing
with your friends at a table,

00:01:37.860 --> 00:01:40.450
your phone is with
you, but it really

00:01:40.450 --> 00:01:44.170
lacks an understanding
of your environments.

00:01:44.170 --> 00:01:47.140
You're limited by the
boundaries of the screen.

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:51.560
And what Project Tango hopes
to do is to break this boundary

00:01:51.560 --> 00:01:54.080
and to bring your phone
and the world more

00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:56.630
in tune with each other.

00:01:56.630 --> 00:02:01.300
So we want to teach phones
to see and understand

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:03.010
their environments.

00:02:03.010 --> 00:02:05.900
And we would like to
augment and improve

00:02:05.900 --> 00:02:08.840
our own ability to
answer questions

00:02:08.840 --> 00:02:11.050
about the world around us.

00:02:11.050 --> 00:02:15.380
Those questions might be things
like, how much paint do I

00:02:15.380 --> 00:02:18.450
need for a wall in
my room if I'm going

00:02:18.450 --> 00:02:21.730
to be repainting my house?

00:02:21.730 --> 00:02:25.400
Or will the couch I'm going
to buy online actually fit

00:02:25.400 --> 00:02:26.320
in my room?

00:02:26.320 --> 00:02:30.190
I recently bought a sleeper
sofa and made a big mistake.

00:02:32.830 --> 00:02:35.720
Or how do I get from
where I am to the laundry

00:02:35.720 --> 00:02:37.060
detergent in a store?

00:02:39.600 --> 00:02:43.240
So Project Tango allows us
to answer these questions

00:02:43.240 --> 00:02:44.720
and more.

00:02:44.720 --> 00:02:47.700
And we use special cameras
and inertial sensors

00:02:47.700 --> 00:02:52.160
that we've built into phones
to make sense of the world

00:02:52.160 --> 00:02:53.630
much like we do.

00:02:53.630 --> 00:02:57.870
And we allow the phone to build
a human-scale understanding

00:02:57.870 --> 00:03:02.040
of space and motion.

00:03:02.040 --> 00:03:05.640
And then we expose this
understanding to application

00:03:05.640 --> 00:03:11.800
developers by adding three core
technologies to mobile devices,

00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:14.640
and I'll talk about each
of them a little bit here.

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:17.320
So the first one
is motion tracking,

00:03:17.320 --> 00:03:23.710
the second is area learning, and
the third is depth perception.

00:03:23.710 --> 00:03:27.710
Motion tracking allows Tango
devices to track their position

00:03:27.710 --> 00:03:29.810
and orientation in space.

00:03:29.810 --> 00:03:32.610
As the phone is moved
through the environments,

00:03:32.610 --> 00:03:36.670
it keeps a log of its trajectory
to within centimeters.

00:03:36.670 --> 00:03:41.340
This works almost like a
mouse but in full six degrees

00:03:41.340 --> 00:03:43.570
of freedom.

00:03:43.570 --> 00:03:47.700
Area learning allows Project
Tango devices to recognize

00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:49.780
where they've been before.

00:03:49.780 --> 00:03:52.870
When a distinctive visual
landmark like a sign,

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:56.720
or a poster, or a
picture is seen,

00:03:56.720 --> 00:03:59.740
the device stores
this in its memory.

00:03:59.740 --> 00:04:03.710
And the next time it or any
other Project Tango device

00:04:03.710 --> 00:04:07.430
sees this visual fingerprint
of sorts, the device

00:04:07.430 --> 00:04:10.720
recognizes its precise
location in the world.

00:04:10.720 --> 00:04:13.390
So I could walk into
a store and recognize

00:04:13.390 --> 00:04:15.630
that I'm at the
checkout register

00:04:15.630 --> 00:04:20.240
just by seeing a sign
above the cashier.

00:04:20.240 --> 00:04:24.980
And the third technology that
we expose is depth perception,

00:04:24.980 --> 00:04:27.150
and this allows
Project Tango devices

00:04:27.150 --> 00:04:30.330
to see the world
in three dimensions

00:04:30.330 --> 00:04:33.430
And we've done this by
adding additional sensors,

00:04:33.430 --> 00:04:37.260
special depth cameras,
to mobile phones.

00:04:37.260 --> 00:04:39.460
This allows your
phone to understand

00:04:39.460 --> 00:04:42.130
the full geometric
structure and also

00:04:42.130 --> 00:04:47.020
the scale-- the metric
scale-- of your environments.

