And I believe they're $399, so
you can today go and preorder

00:25:12.730 --> 00:25:16.740
an Intel RealSense device that
has Project Tango capabilities.

00:25:16.740 --> 00:25:19.130
And we're working with them
as well as our other chipset

00:25:19.130 --> 00:25:21.440
partners.

00:25:21.440 --> 00:25:22.310
Other questions?

00:25:22.310 --> 00:25:24.977
You in the front
row in the back.

00:25:24.977 --> 00:25:25.560
AUDIENCE: Yes.

00:25:25.560 --> 00:25:28.260
Do you see a future with
Project Tango and gaming

00:25:28.260 --> 00:25:31.035
with Google Cardboard, for
example-- virtual headset,

00:25:31.035 --> 00:25:32.564
you know, [INAUDIBLE] HMDs?

00:25:32.564 --> 00:25:33.730
EITAN MARDER-EPPSTEIN: Yeah.

00:25:33.730 --> 00:25:35.480
So I think Project--
the question

00:25:35.480 --> 00:25:38.450
was do you see a future for
Project Tango with gaming?

00:25:38.450 --> 00:25:41.310
And I think that
there is a huge future

00:25:41.310 --> 00:25:43.680
for Project Tango with gaming.

00:25:43.680 --> 00:25:45.860
I think there's
also a huge future

00:25:45.860 --> 00:25:52.090
for using Project Tango for any
kind of positional tracking.

00:25:52.090 --> 00:25:54.170
And you can think about
extensions to that.

00:25:54.170 --> 00:25:58.540
We've played around with taking
it and putting it in an HMD.

00:25:58.540 --> 00:26:01.890
There are other problems
with that like screen refresh

00:26:01.890 --> 00:26:06.450
latency and all of the problems
that come along with that.

00:26:06.450 --> 00:26:09.830
But I do think that people will
use the devices in that way,

00:26:09.830 --> 00:26:13.920
and it's really
interesting to me.

00:26:13.920 --> 00:26:14.835
Yes.

00:26:14.835 --> 00:26:16.775
AUDIENCE: Can you use
that device [INAUDIBLE]

00:26:16.775 --> 00:26:20.170
will up your-- outdoor
with a lot of trees

00:26:20.170 --> 00:26:22.110
and wind in the [INAUDIBLE]?

00:26:22.110 --> 00:26:23.568
EITAN MARDER-EPPSTEIN:
The question

00:26:23.568 --> 00:26:25.160
was will Project
Tango work outdoors?

00:26:25.160 --> 00:26:28.080
And the answer there is
that pieces of the stack

00:26:28.080 --> 00:26:30.780
will work outdoors,
so the motion tracking

00:26:30.780 --> 00:26:34.560
and area learning capabilities
will work outdoors.

00:26:34.560 --> 00:26:36.490
But depth perception--

00:26:36.490 --> 00:26:38.120
AUDIENCE: Trees, leaves, and--

00:26:38.120 --> 00:26:38.290
EITAN MARDER-EPPSTEIN: Yeah.

00:26:38.290 --> 00:26:40.260
Trees and leaves are
actually great features

00:26:40.260 --> 00:26:42.350
to track as you move
through the world,

00:26:42.350 --> 00:26:44.430
but the problem is the sun.

00:26:44.430 --> 00:26:47.390
The sun turns out to be a
really, really strong source

00:26:47.390 --> 00:26:48.890
of infrared light.

00:26:48.890 --> 00:26:50.690
And so for the
depth sensors that

00:26:50.690 --> 00:26:52.390
are currently on
the Tango tablet,

00:26:52.390 --> 00:26:54.410
they get overpowered by the sun.

00:26:54.410 --> 00:26:58.370
So you would be able to do
outdoor navigation with a Tango

00:26:58.370 --> 00:27:01.680
device but having Mittens
follow you through the trees,

00:27:01.680 --> 00:27:03.965
unless you were in a shaded
area, would be difficult.

00:27:03.965 --> 00:27:07.721
AUDIENCE: What about lenses--
special filtered lenses

00:27:07.721 --> 00:27:10.271
to filter out
overwhelming [INAUDIBLE]?

00:27:10.271 --> 00:27:11.770
EITAN MARDER-EPPSTEIN:
Well, I think

00:27:11.770 --> 00:27:14.660
the problem with using
specialized lenses to filter

00:27:14.660 --> 00:27:17.020
out IR, which is
something that you can do,

00:27:17.020 --> 00:27:21.290
is that the device needs to see
the IR pattern to be able to do

00:27:21.290 --> 00:27:22.900
its depth computation.

00:27:22.900 --> 00:27:24.870
And so if you
filter out that IR,

00:27:24.870 --> 00:27:27.390
the device doesn't
see the pattern.

00:27:27.390 --> 00:27:29.139
There are solutions to this.

00:27:29.139 --> 00:27:29.930
AUDIENCE: --sensor.

00:27:29.930 --> 00:27:31.870
EITAN MARDER-EPPSTEIN: Yes,
it depends on the sensors.

00:27:31.870 --> 00:27:33.000
The current sensors-- no.

00:27:33.000 --> 00:27:37.080
But over time we hope to improve
the ability of these devices

00:27:37.080 --> 00:27:39.460
to see outdoors.

00:27:39.460 --> 00:27:41.160
Other questions?

00:27:41.160 --> 00:27:43.182
Yes, you next to
the blue-- yeah.

