EITAN MARDER-EPPSTEIN:
So the question

00:28:30.880 --> 00:28:34.210
was will Tango technology
be extended into other form

00:28:34.210 --> 00:28:35.940
factors like robotics?

00:28:35.940 --> 00:28:38.140
I think absolutely yes.

00:28:38.140 --> 00:28:38.910
Well, I hope so.

00:28:38.910 --> 00:28:40.640
My background's
actually in robotics,

00:28:40.640 --> 00:28:44.760
so I have a little bit
of an interest in this.

00:28:44.760 --> 00:28:47.140
But we've already had
interest from people

00:28:47.140 --> 00:28:49.420
who are doing
quadrotors-- anyone who

00:28:49.420 --> 00:28:52.360
needs a light
weight localization

00:28:52.360 --> 00:28:54.490
solution on their device.

00:28:54.490 --> 00:28:57.810
I think there's huge
impact potential there.

00:28:57.810 --> 00:29:00.290
We're really focusing
on the smartphone space

00:29:00.290 --> 00:29:03.610
first to drive down the
cost of these sensors

00:29:03.610 --> 00:29:05.972
and to make the technology
more ubiquitous.

00:29:05.972 --> 00:29:08.120
We believe that that's
the best way to get it out

00:29:08.120 --> 00:29:10.010
into the world, and then
things like robotics

00:29:10.010 --> 00:29:11.850
can piggyback on top of it.

00:29:11.850 --> 00:29:13.140
All right.

